548
00:32:54,540 --> 00:32:56,573
Had a real nasty scar

549
00:32:56,575 --> 00:32:58,442
on the left side
of his face,

550
00:32:58,444 --> 00:33:03,180
what was his name?
We ain't in no hurry, is we?

551
00:33:03,182 --> 00:33:06,683
What was his name?
I said, we ain't in no hurry.

552
00:33:06,685 --> 00:33:09,720
[Chuckles]

553
00:33:09,722 --> 00:33:12,723
Where was I?

554
00:33:12,725 --> 00:33:15,158
Oh, yeah.

555
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:17,728
This fellow
claimed that, uh,

556
00:33:17,730 --> 00:33:20,731
the gunshot to the head
almost killed him.

557
00:33:20,733 --> 00:33:23,700
Bank robbery
gone wrong, says he.

558
00:33:23,702 --> 00:33:25,736
Convinced this lawman

559
00:33:25,738 --> 00:33:27,738
to go along with him
on account of

560
00:33:27,740 --> 00:33:30,073
he had a fine piece of ass

561
00:33:30,075 --> 00:33:32,409
held hostage,
and he was gonna kill her.

562
00:33:32,411 --> 00:33:34,778
If the lawman didn't
go along with him.

563
00:33:34,780 --> 00:33:36,380
I need your help, Duke.

564
00:33:36,382 --> 00:33:38,515
Put your gun down, or I'm
blowing her head right off!

565
00:33:38,517 --> 00:33:40,617
He's gonna kill me!
Put your gun down!

566
00:33:40,619 --> 00:33:44,454
Good.
I need your help.

567
00:33:44,456 --> 00:33:47,324
Keep talking.
Well...

568
00:33:48,760 --> 00:33:51,495
Anyhow, they
pulled off the robbery

569
00:33:51,497 --> 00:33:52,696
and got back to the hideout.

570
00:33:52,698 --> 00:33:54,698
And they thought this lawman

571
00:33:54,700 --> 00:33:56,233
was gonna be easy pickings,

572
00:33:56,235 --> 00:33:57,701
on account of he was
outnumbered and all,

573
00:33:57,703 --> 00:34:00,637
but...

574
00:34:00,639 --> 00:34:03,440
They was wrong.

575
00:34:05,043 --> 00:34:07,344
Come on! Let's go! Hah!

576
00:34:08,379 --> 00:34:12,282
Aah!

577
00:34:12,284 --> 00:34:14,618
Whoa!

578
00:34:14,620 --> 00:34:16,586
Aah!

579
00:34:30,668 --> 00:34:33,437
Dark irony, it was.

580
00:34:33,439 --> 00:34:35,305
Seems that this lawman

581
00:34:35,307 --> 00:34:37,541
and the woman
he was trying to help

582
00:34:37,543 --> 00:34:39,543
was actually the very woman

583
00:34:39,545 --> 00:34:42,279
who betrayed him.

584
00:34:42,281 --> 00:34:44,114
She was a painted lady.

585
00:34:44,116 --> 00:34:47,751
Lover of levi hardin.

586
00:34:47,753 --> 00:34:51,154
Nursed him back to health.

587
00:34:51,156 --> 00:34:53,557
Was in on it all along.

588
00:34:53,559 --> 00:34:55,459
What happened to him?

589
00:34:55,461 --> 00:34:56,626
Where is he?

590
00:34:56,628 --> 00:34:59,262
That's, uh--
that's the best part, see?

591
00:34:59,264 --> 00:35:01,531
Hardin was caught
stealing cattle

592
00:35:01,533 --> 00:35:03,233
in that part of country.

593
00:35:03,235 --> 00:35:04,835
That's a hangable offense.

594
00:35:04,837 --> 00:35:07,737
[Crowd]
♪ hallelujah

595
00:35:07,739 --> 00:35:10,574
♪ hallelujah

596
00:35:12,577 --> 00:35:15,612
♪ hallelujah

597
00:35:15,614 --> 00:35:20,217
♪ hallelujah

598
00:35:23,521 --> 00:35:24,688
sheriff?

599
00:35:24,690 --> 00:35:26,389
Levi Perry hardin,

600
00:35:26,391 --> 00:35:28,225
you have been
sentenced by a jury

601
00:35:28,227 --> 00:35:30,393
to hang for your crimes

602
00:35:30,395 --> 00:35:32,129
until dead.

603
00:35:32,131 --> 00:35:34,131
Do you have any last words?

604
00:35:40,738 --> 00:35:42,205
Yeah.

605
00:35:42,207 --> 00:35:44,474
Y'all can kiss my ass!

606
00:35:44,476 --> 00:35:46,243
[Crowd gasps]

607
00:35:46,245 --> 00:35:49,146
[Man grunts]
[Crowd screams]

608
00:36:10,935 --> 00:36:12,736
Yeah! Hyah!

609
00:36:20,344 --> 00:36:22,379
It's just funny how

610
00:36:22,381 --> 00:36:25,916
a man can kill innocent
women and children

611
00:36:25,918 --> 00:36:29,386
and get life in prison.

612
00:36:29,388 --> 00:36:31,755
But you take a man's cow?

613
00:36:31,757 --> 00:36:33,390
[Laughs]

614
00:36:33,392 --> 00:36:35,725
That's a whole 'nother
goddamn deal, ain't it?

615
00:36:39,564 --> 00:36:42,666
Guard!

616
00:36:42,668 --> 00:36:44,568
Guard!

617
00:36:49,407 --> 00:36:50,941
You tell the warden

618
00:36:50,943 --> 00:36:53,543
I'm ready to see him.

619
00:37:08,859 --> 00:37:11,294
Well, prisoner Donovan.

620
00:37:11,296 --> 00:37:13,797
This is a pleasant surprise.

621
00:37:15,800 --> 00:37:18,435
Leave us.

622
00:37:23,674 --> 00:37:25,942
I must commend you.

623
00:37:25,944 --> 00:37:28,578
You and your friend
lasted a good while.

624
00:37:28,580 --> 00:37:31,615
Not as long as some,
mind you,

625
00:37:31,617 --> 00:37:34,951
but then, they didn't
have the choice you did.

626
00:37:34,953 --> 00:37:36,453
I came here to tell you

627
00:37:36,455 --> 00:37:38,888
that levi hardin
is still alive.

628
00:37:38,890 --> 00:37:42,525
And I think I know
where he's headed next.

629
00:37:42,527 --> 00:37:43,693
Excuse me?

630
00:37:43,695 --> 00:37:45,996
That's what you
came to say to me?

631
00:37:45,998 --> 00:37:48,531
Did you hear what I said?

632
00:37:48,533 --> 00:37:50,934
Hardin's still alive.

633
00:37:50,936 --> 00:37:54,838
I think my wife's in danger.

634
00:37:54,840 --> 00:37:58,441
Well, that is a predicament.

635
00:37:58,443 --> 00:38:00,477
But I fail to see
what that has to do

636
00:38:00,479 --> 00:38:02,012
with our meeting here today.

637
00:38:02,014 --> 00:38:03,680
Listen, you son of a bitch!

638
00:38:03,682 --> 00:38:06,283
I don't care
what you think of me.

639
00:38:06,285 --> 00:38:08,351
My wife's in danger.

640
00:38:08,353 --> 00:38:09,619
Hardin's not gonna stop till

641
00:38:09,621 --> 00:38:11,321
he gets to me
any way he knows how!

642
00:38:11,323 --> 00:38:13,023
Now, you gotta do something!

643
00:38:13,025 --> 00:38:14,991
I suggest
you take your hands

644
00:38:14,993 --> 00:38:17,694
off my collar.

645
00:38:17,696 --> 00:38:20,363
One call from me,
and you won't have to worry

646
00:38:20,365 --> 00:38:22,499
about your precious wife.

647
00:38:22,501 --> 00:38:25,568
Because you'll be dead.

648
00:38:35,646 --> 00:38:37,647
Excellent.

649
00:38:37,649 --> 00:38:41,384
Guard!

650
00:38:41,386 --> 00:38:42,786
Take him away.

651
00:38:42,788 --> 00:38:45,789
No, put him in with
the main population.

652
00:38:45,791 --> 00:38:48,525
I'm sure they'll
make room for him.

653
00:38:48,527 --> 00:38:49,893
I don't care
what you think of me.

654
00:38:49,895 --> 00:38:52,329
There's an innocent woman
in danger.

655
00:38:52,331 --> 00:38:54,097
It's your duty to help her!

656
00:38:54,099 --> 00:38:56,433
It's your duty!
I have a witness!

657
00:38:56,435 --> 00:38:58,802
Ask Dalton!

658
00:38:58,804 --> 00:39:00,704
Ask Dalton!

659
00:39:03,541 --> 00:39:06,076
They will crucify him, sir.

660
00:39:06,078 --> 00:39:08,478
Do it.

661
00:39:11,749 --> 00:39:14,918
[Moans] Cy,

662
00:39:14,920 --> 00:39:16,419
you do make the best ribs

663
00:39:16,421 --> 00:39:19,689
this side
of the Mississippi.

664
00:39:19,691 --> 00:39:20,924
Hmm.

665
00:39:26,697 --> 00:39:28,598
Look, Sullivan,
as far as I can tell,

666
00:39:28,600 --> 00:39:30,100
you're the only guy
in here that has

667
00:39:30,102 --> 00:39:31,801
some sense
of right and wrong.

668
00:39:31,803 --> 00:39:35,705
Now, if you won't
help me, help her.

669
00:39:35,707 --> 00:39:37,607
Unhook him.

670
00:39:37,609 --> 00:39:40,844
She's all alone
out there, Sullivan.

671
00:39:42,980 --> 00:39:45,782
You gotta help her--
you gotta do something!

672
00:39:45,784 --> 00:39:48,651
There ain't nothing
I can do, goddamn it!

673
00:39:49,987 --> 00:39:52,489
What the hell
am I supposed to do, huh?

674
00:39:54,992 --> 00:39:57,861
Go on.

675
00:39:57,863 --> 00:39:59,929
Go!

676
00:40:03,834 --> 00:40:06,436
Go!

677
00:40:10,074 --> 00:40:13,543
Go, please.

678
00:40:16,414 --> 00:40:19,416
Son of a bitch.

679
00:40:27,858 --> 00:40:29,626
Mr. Donovan.

680
00:40:29,628 --> 00:40:32,896
I got me a nice place
right over here for you.

681
00:40:32,898 --> 00:40:36,499
You know, first thing
I did when I got out

682
00:40:36,501 --> 00:40:39,569
was make a trade for this.

683
00:40:41,005 --> 00:40:44,474
Hey, Donovan.

684
00:40:44,476 --> 00:40:46,776
What's going on?

685
00:40:49,180 --> 00:40:51,014
You need to get
out of here, kid.

686
00:40:51,016 --> 00:40:53,817
No matter what happens,
you stay away.

687
00:40:53,819 --> 00:40:56,886
No, sir, I need to stay
right here with you.

688
00:40:56,888 --> 00:40:59,055
Beat it.

689
00:40:59,057 --> 00:41:01,791
Beat it!

690
00:41:01,793 --> 00:41:04,828
What you gonna do?

691
00:41:04,830 --> 00:41:06,062
I'm not sure.

692
00:41:06,064 --> 00:41:08,097
You remember me?

693
00:41:08,099 --> 00:41:10,834
Oh yeah, I remember you.

694
00:41:10,836 --> 00:41:13,937
Jarvison.

695
00:41:13,939 --> 00:41:16,473
You and your rapist brother.

696
00:41:16,475 --> 00:41:18,174
It ain't proper
to insult the dead

697
00:41:18,176 --> 00:41:20,543
since you done the killin'.

698
00:41:20,545 --> 00:41:23,213
Kid, I want you
to promise me something.

699
00:41:23,215 --> 00:41:25,181
Yes, sir.

700
00:41:25,183 --> 00:41:27,684
No matter what
happens to me,

701
00:41:27,686 --> 00:41:30,119
you hang in there.

702
00:41:30,121 --> 00:41:31,588
You stick with
the old-timers.

703
00:41:31,590 --> 00:41:33,056
They know how to survive.

704
00:41:33,058 --> 00:41:34,757
Yeah.
You hear me?

705
00:41:34,759 --> 00:41:37,627
Uh-huh. But you
gonna be okay?

706
00:41:39,230 --> 00:41:40,797
Just promise me.

707
00:41:40,799 --> 00:41:43,099
Yes, sir.

708
00:41:47,805 --> 00:41:50,707
Let it be.

709
00:41:50,709 --> 00:41:54,844
[Prisoners cheer, yell]

710
00:41:54,846 --> 00:41:58,114
Yeah! Go!

711
00:41:58,116 --> 00:42:00,083
Come on, Mr. Donovan!

712
00:42:00,085 --> 00:42:01,985
Watch out!

713
00:42:22,306 --> 00:42:24,874
Come on. Come on.

714
00:42:24,876 --> 00:42:26,843
Yeah.
Come on.

715
00:42:40,291 --> 00:42:42,725
Take it-- take it easy.

716
00:42:48,866 --> 00:42:50,266
Come on.

717
00:42:50,268 --> 00:42:52,035
Come on, come on.

718
00:42:52,037 --> 00:42:55,038
Hang in with me, now.

719
00:42:55,040 --> 00:42:57,006
It's all right, kid.

720
00:43:37,348 --> 00:43:40,883
You give him
a decent burial.

721
00:43:59,937 --> 00:44:01,904
Ladies!

722
00:44:01,906 --> 00:44:03,172
Lockdown.

723
00:44:03,174 --> 00:44:05,775
Night-night time.

724
00:44:18,255 --> 00:44:20,723
[Cyrus]
Checkin' the locks.

725
00:44:25,029 --> 00:44:27,130
Checking locks.

726
00:44:28,999 --> 00:44:31,134
Donovan.

727
00:44:36,974 --> 00:44:38,941
You don't belong here.

728
00:44:38,943 --> 00:44:42,011
Meet me at
the new yard in one hour.

729
00:44:42,013 --> 00:44:43,746
You get caught,

730
00:44:43,748 --> 00:44:45,415
you're on your own.

731
00:44:45,417 --> 00:44:48,117
[Coyote howls]

732
00:44:54,258 --> 00:44:56,292
Checkin' locks.

733
00:45:02,366 --> 00:45:04,133
Hey! Hey!

734
00:45:04,135 --> 00:45:06,869
Come on.

735
00:45:06,871 --> 00:45:08,438
Get down! Get down.

736
00:45:08,440 --> 00:45:12,141
Now, look.

737
00:45:12,143 --> 00:45:15,311
This, this tunnel will
take you into the cemetery,

738
00:45:15,313 --> 00:45:18,314
under the wall, and come out
by the warden's stables.

739
00:45:18,316 --> 00:45:20,917
There's a set of reins
there waiting for you.

740
00:45:20,919 --> 00:45:23,186
The warden had this dug
in case there was ever a mutiny.

741
00:45:23,188 --> 00:45:24,787
What about you?
Oh, no.

742
00:45:24,789 --> 00:45:27,323
My runnin' days--
they behind me.

743
00:45:27,325 --> 00:45:28,791
You just get on.

744
00:45:28,793 --> 00:45:30,827
Rescue your lady.

745
00:45:30,829 --> 00:45:33,930
Hey, Donovan.

746
00:45:33,932 --> 00:45:36,165
I'm real sorry
about that kid.

747
00:45:36,167 --> 00:45:38,034
Now, go on,
get to getting, cause...

748
00:45:38,036 --> 00:45:41,471
Them guards'll be starting
a new set of rounds soon.

749
00:45:41,473 --> 00:45:43,406
Cyrus, you could
get hung for this.

750
00:45:43,408 --> 00:45:45,942
No, don't worry about me.

751
00:45:45,944 --> 00:45:48,044
I'll be all right.

752
00:46:54,344 --> 00:46:56,813
[Horse whinnies]

753
00:47:02,886 --> 00:47:05,221
[Hammer clicks]
[Man grunts]

754
00:47:09,293 --> 00:47:12,829
I thought you said
your running days were over.

755
00:47:13,831 --> 00:47:16,299
I changed my mind.

756
00:47:48,465 --> 00:47:51,067
[Horse neighs]

757
00:48:16,894 --> 00:48:20,496
♪ Well, I was
shaken from my sleep ♪

758
00:48:20,498 --> 00:48:22,098
♪ as they dragged me

759
00:48:22,100 --> 00:48:25,468
♪ to my feet

760
00:48:25,470 --> 00:48:27,303
♪ I was mistaken

761
00:48:27,305 --> 00:48:31,007
♪ by the long arm
of the law ♪

762
00:48:32,509 --> 00:48:34,210
♪ and the lesson

763
00:48:34,212 --> 00:48:36,279
♪ I have learned

764
00:48:36,281 --> 00:48:40,249
♪ is the innocent
get burned ♪

765
00:48:40,251 --> 00:48:43,519
♪ and the guilty
set you up ♪

766
00:48:43,521 --> 00:48:46,489
♪ to take the fall

767
00:48:53,130 --> 00:48:56,966
♪ nobody's guilty in here

768
00:48:56,968 --> 00:48:58,634
♪ and the truth
ain't always ♪

769
00:48:58,636 --> 00:49:01,437
♪ how it appears

770
00:49:01,439 --> 00:49:04,006
♪ our story's
all the same ♪

771
00:49:04,008 --> 00:49:07,476
♪ lord knows
we've all been framed ♪

772
00:49:07,478 --> 00:49:08,711
♪ and the evidence

773
00:49:08,713 --> 00:49:12,315
♪ is perfectly clear

774
00:49:12,317 --> 00:49:15,952
♪ nobody's guilty in here

775
00:49:40,344 --> 00:49:42,044
sorry to trouble you,
ma'am.

776
00:49:42,046 --> 00:49:43,679
Got a man hurt.

777
00:49:43,681 --> 00:49:45,715
Can we use your well?

778
00:49:45,717 --> 00:49:47,583
Please?

779
00:49:50,520 --> 00:49:52,488
Bring him inside.

780
00:50:06,003 --> 00:50:07,737
Whoa, you know.

781
00:50:07,739 --> 00:50:11,207
We'd better water
these horses.

782
00:50:11,209 --> 00:50:13,275
There's ain't no time.

783
00:50:13,277 --> 00:50:15,144
Well, if we
don't water them,

784
00:50:15,146 --> 00:50:17,380
we're gonna be walking.

785
00:50:17,382 --> 00:50:19,048
All right.

786
00:50:27,257 --> 00:50:29,492
Who was it?
Donovan.

787
00:50:29,494 --> 00:50:31,227
And cy, too.

788
00:50:31,229 --> 00:50:33,496
Cy?

789
00:50:33,498 --> 00:50:36,098
Goddamn nigger.

790
00:50:36,100 --> 00:50:37,767
Bring them back.

791
00:50:37,769 --> 00:50:40,102
Dead.

792
00:50:46,610 --> 00:50:48,477
Put him over there.

793
00:51:04,261 --> 00:51:08,397
Get me some towels.

794
00:51:08,399 --> 00:51:10,199
Well...

795
00:51:10,201 --> 00:51:13,369
It's a real pretty place.

796
00:51:13,371 --> 00:51:15,471
Yep.

797
00:51:15,473 --> 00:51:17,673
Whoa. [Groans]

798
00:51:17,675 --> 00:51:21,277
Ahh. Thank you.

799
00:51:21,279 --> 00:51:23,612
Not much further, friend.

800
00:51:26,283 --> 00:51:28,117
I'll tell you
one thing, Cyrus.

801
00:51:28,119 --> 00:51:29,785
You sure don't
ride like a cook.

802
00:51:29,787 --> 00:51:31,487
That's 'cause I ain't one.

803
00:51:31,489 --> 00:51:33,422
Well, the warden
sure liked your cooking.

804
00:51:33,424 --> 00:51:37,159
Yeah, well, that's 'cause
of my special sauce.

805
00:51:38,095 --> 00:51:39,495
Oh, special sauce, huh?

806
00:51:39,497 --> 00:51:42,865
You don't wanna know.
[Both laugh]

807
00:51:42,867 --> 00:51:44,567
So what happened, anyway?

808
00:51:44,569 --> 00:51:45,868
What happened to what?

809
00:51:45,870 --> 00:51:48,504
To get you thrown
in that rat-hole prison?

810
00:51:48,506 --> 00:51:51,107
Oh, well.

811
00:51:51,109 --> 00:51:52,441
I was in the ninth.

812
00:51:52,443 --> 00:51:54,176
You're a sure-enough
buffalo soldier.

813
00:51:54,178 --> 00:51:56,378
That's right.
That's colonel hatch,

814
00:51:56,380 --> 00:51:59,248
wasn't it?
Yes, sir.

815
00:51:59,250 --> 00:52:01,517
You know, we had us
this old buck sergeant.

816
00:52:01,519 --> 00:52:04,854
I mean, he wanted to ride me
all the way to Kansas City.

817
00:52:04,856 --> 00:52:07,857
Busting me down
to a dog...

818
00:52:07,859 --> 00:52:09,358
Made you a cook, did he?

819
00:52:09,360 --> 00:52:12,128
Yeah, I don't
like being a cook.

820
00:52:12,130 --> 00:52:14,163
Let me ask you
